format:
A data frame with 1,136 rows representing individual bakers per
episode and 4 variables:
reference:
See
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Great_British_Bake_Off_(series_1)#Results_summary,
for example, for series 1 results summary.
description:
Description
This data has one row per baker for every episode,
including episodes they did not appear in.
title: Each baker's results by episode (raw)

parameters.baker:
A character string giving given or nickname only (note: see
bakers for full baker names)
parameters.episode: A factor denoting episode number within a series
parameters.result:
A factor denoting if the baker was "IN", "OUT",
"STAR BAKER", or "SICK" for a given episode. For finale episodes,
values are either "WINNER" or "RUNNER-UP". If NA, baker did not
appear in episode.
